History: His-Story -
Blame Hollywood, the media, and even history books and teachers for perpetuating certain totally ridiculous or unfounded """"facts"""" about history.
-
Vikings didn’t have have horns on their helmets, iron maidens aren’t real, Columbus didn’t prove the world is round, Napoleon wasn’t short, Paul Revere didn’t shout “the British are coming,” Isaac Newton wasn’t hit by an apple, Walt Disney didn’t draw Mickey Mouse, Nero didn’t fiddle over a burning Rome and “Et tu, Brute?“ doesn’t have the historical significance you think it does. -
-
And that’s just the beginning, examples listed above are only basic examples. If you research enough you can find that many of our history “lessons” and modern day beliefs about our past were completely fabricated. Wars, assassinations, mass genocide, Cultures, ancestors, Nephilim. Many things have been covered up and re written to hide the truth in our past historical events, discoveries and much much more.
